  <p>Block 2 makes the energy balance quantitative. Students calculate planetary temperature under different greenhouse-gas concentrations using simple energy-balance equations (incoming solar flux, planetary albedo, Stefan-Boltzmann radiation). The point: temperature sensitivity to CO₂ isn't a vibe — it's a number you can derive. Exit: temperature predictions for Earth at 280, 420, and 560 ppm CO₂.</p>
